3 I've done breakfast here a time or two. I do totally enjoy the fact that the oj is bottomless but its no butterfields fresh squeezed thats for sure! The prices are good, especially for the over 55. They also have a decent under 500 calorie breakfast selection. I ordered the nut pancakes!! Wow I was pleasantly surprised with how good they actually tasted and the egg subsitution was better than a lot of other restaurants! Its nothing over the top amazing but it works if you are in the area, especially over IHOP or Dennys.  And check out their pies! MMMMMMmmm good for a chain pie and definitely beats out the freezer kinds!
