3 I have never been to a Coco's I didn't like.  Although,. the night my husband and I went to this one, it seemed like everything went wrong.  First, there was no Prime Rib available. This was written on the sandwich board at the front. Yet, the main menu was all Prime Rib. "There's no prime rib?" my husband quipped with the waitress.  She said because he asked she would give him a 50% off coupon for his next visit. Apparently, there was an issue with the restaurant not getting enough from their supplier. The meal was pretty good. The waitress was incredibly sweet and friendly. My husband had a craving for pie. He ordered a peach pie.  The waitress came back with the pie and showed us that it was not made well. Instead of syrupy, the peaches were more like water. She said they had a new baker and she had been avoiding selling the peach pie all day, because of this. She made a suggestion of another pie, then went to check on it. When she came back, she gave us another discount coupon and said she felt so bad about not having anything we ordered.   We will definitely come back, again, though.  Sometimes a lacking on food can be made up by great customer service.   Hope we get the same waitress again.
